FBIS4-27044 "drchi125_h_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-125 Daily Report 29 Jun 1994 West Europe Diplomatic Relations Established With Andorra Diplomatic Relations Established With Andorra OW2906093894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0926 GMT 29 Jun 94 OW2906093894 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Madrid, June 29 (XINHUA) -- China and Andorra today formally established diplomatic relations. A communique to the effect was signed in Andorra City today by Chinese Ambassador to Spain Song Guoqing and Andorran Foreign Minister Marc Vila Amigo [name as received]. The communique said, "the two governments agree to develop relations of friendship and cooperation between the two countries on the basis of mutual respect of sovereignty and territorial integrity, non-aggression, non-interference in each other's internal affairs, equality and mutual benefit, and peaceful coexistence." "The government of the Principality of Andorra recognizes that the Government of the People's Republic of China is the only legitimate government of China and that Taiwan is an inalienable part of the territory of China," said the communique.
